{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"SCOPE REFINEMENT (acceptance criterion): the completion verifier must be skipped for a duplicate/supersedes closure IF AND ONLY IF the ticket carries a VALID 'supersedes' or 'duplicates' link to another ticket. It is NOT a blanket exemption for the --class value alone: a --class duplicate/not_a_bug/escalated close with NO valid superseding/duplicating link MUST still run completion verification (else it becomes a trivial bypass). The exemption is gated on the existence of a valid link to another ticket, not on the class string."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784509342278172001,"uuid":"3a921ef6-bae3-46ec-90e6-80c93cb8514b"}